data.description: GREAT NEWS; the seller has agreed to lower their asking price to $749,900. Additional good news...the existing mortgage is assumable at a lower rate than the market's prevailing rates. Welcome to 5715 Whitewater Street, an inviting residence nestled within the prestigious Green Hills community and the excellent school district of Yorba Linda. This delightful home features 3 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms, ensuring a comfortable and cozy living experience for you and your family. With a solid foundation already in place, here lies the ideal fixer-upper opportunity, allowing you to infuse your unique style and creativity to craft your dream home in this serene and highly sought-after neighborhood.    Upon entry, your eyes will be drawn to the captivating cathedral ceiling adorned with a charming wood beam that stretches gracefully across the family room ceiling. It's a perfect canvas for you to add your personal touch and transform this house into your dream home. Notable upgrades include a newer A/C unit, garage door and dual-paned windows, ensuring energy efficiency while flooding the home with natural light, creating an inviting ambiance. To truly appreciate the charm of this residence, we highly recommend an in-person viewing.    Step into the quaint and private backyard, where you can savor moments of tranquility and relaxation. It's a hidden oasis waiting for you to make your own. Beyond the comforts of this charming home, you'll also enjoy the convenience of a nearby park and playground, providing a delightful outdoor space for leisure and recreation for the whole family.    Adding to the allure, the garage is a great man?-cave, perfect for indulging in hobbies and relaxation, with notable features that include a workbench and air conditioning. The modest HOA dues of $90 per month encompass a secure area for residents to store their recreational vehicles, including RVs, boats, and jet skis, offering both convenience and peace of mind. An incredible opportunity awaits you to make this lovely home your very own, one where you can create lasting memories with your loved ones.    It's worth noting that model-match comparable homes in the same tract recently closed for $825,000 on 8/23/23 and $863,000 on 6/01/23. Act swiftly to seize this chance to embark on your journey of homeownership in this gem of an opportunity.
